item.title: Whispers of Dawn
item.media:title: Whispers of Dawn
item.media:description: This serene photograph captures a tranquil lake scene at what appears to be either dawn or dusk. A soft mist hovers just above the perfectly still water, creating a seamless, almost mirror-like reflection of the faint sky and the distant, tree-lined shore. The minimal composition, dominated by the expansive water and subtle transition to the mistyhorizon, evokes a powerful sense of peace, solitude, and ethereal beauty.

item.title: Evening Elegy
item.media:title: Evening Elegy
item.media:description:
I recently came across this rather old shot while digging through one of my (many) folders of unedited images. To my surprise, I had never shared it anywhere before.


I really like it, though it has all my favorite elements of nature photography: a colorful evening sky, a forest, and a veil of mist in the background.

item.title: It's not easy to get yourself back
item.media:title: It's not easy to get yourself back
item.media:description:
It's not easy to get yourself back but I didn't give up. The path I'm following isn't easy. I often feel fear. But today that fear doesn't paralyze me. I face it head on. I overcome my weaknesses and prove to myself how strong I am. I remember who I used to be.. Today, I am even stronger, wiser. I feel complete. But I know also that this path never ends.

The path calls me to go further. So... I'm continuing on my way. : )

item.title: The magical forest of Funal - Madeira 8
item.media:title: The magical forest of Funal - Madeira 8
item.media:description: Fanal Forest is an ancient laurel forest. In 1999, it was included on the UNESCO World Heritage List, and a year later in 2000 it was included on the NATURA 2000 list. These are certainly two great distinctions for this place. Not everyone knows, but this place has also been called a reserve of silence and rest. Throughout the entire area you will also find hiking trails, camping sites and attention - the remains of a small volcanic crater, which is covered with water in winter. From the perspective of tourists visiting this place - it is also famous for having two faces - mysterious and even scary - in the fog or friendly and joyful - in full sun.
